#: inc/class-settings-catalog.php:30
msgid "Custom dashboard"
msgstr ""

#: inc/class-settings-catalog.php:31
msgid ""
"Replace the WordPress dashboard with a custom one: greeting, quick actions, "
"stat tiles, recent activity, site health and storage. Off restores the "
"native dashboard."
msgstr ""

#: inc/class-settings-catalog.php:36
msgid "Notification center"
msgstr ""

#: inc/class-settings-catalog.php:37
msgid ""
"Adds a bell to the toolbar that collects admin notices into a side drawer, "
"keeping success confirmations inline. Off restores every notice to its "
"normal place."
msgstr ""

#: inc/class-settings-catalog.php:42
msgid "Post previews"
msgstr ""

#: inc/class-settings-catalog.php:43
msgid ""
"Adds a thumbnail column to post-type list tables — the featured image first, "
"with a live WordPress.com mShots screenshot as fallback on production sites "
"(skipped on localhost where mShots can't reach the page anyway)."
msgstr ""

#: inc/class-settings-catalog.php:48
msgid "Active plugins first"
msgstr ""

#: inc/class-settings-catalog.php:49
msgid ""
"Sort active plugins to the top of the plugins list so what's running is "
"always in view. Off keeps WordPress's alphabetical order."
msgstr ""

#: inc/class-settings-catalog.php:54
msgid "Open plugins on \"Active\""
msgstr ""

#: inc/class-settings-catalog.php:55
msgid ""
"Land on the \"Active\" filter when you open the plugins list, instead of "
"\"All\". Falls back to \"All\" when no plugins are active. Off keeps the "
"default \"All\" view."
msgstr ""

#: inc/class-settings-catalog.php:60
msgid "Dark mode"
msgstr ""

#: inc/class-settings-catalog.php:61
msgid ""
"Adds a light/dark toggle to the admin bar. Off forces light mode site-wide."
msgstr ""

#: inc/class-settings-catalog.php:66
msgid "Login screen"
msgstr ""

#: inc/class-settings-catalog.php:67
msgid ""
"Restyle wp-login.php to match the admin (logo, dark mode, focus states)."
msgstr ""

#: inc/class-settings-catalog.php:72
msgid "Block editor"
msgstr ""

#: inc/class-settings-catalog.php:73
msgid ""
"Theme the Gutenberg canvas in light and dark. Off keeps the canvas matching "
"your live site exactly."
msgstr ""

#: inc/class-settings-catalog.php:78
msgid "AdminKit icons"
msgstr ""

#: inc/class-settings-catalog.php:79
msgid ""
"Swap WordPress's menu and toolbar icons for AdminKit's set. Icons customised "
"elsewhere (e.g. Admin Menu Editor) are left alone."
msgstr ""

#: inc/class-settings-catalog.php:84
msgid "Menu manager"
msgstr ""

#: inc/class-settings-catalog.php:85
msgid ""
"Reorder the admin menu and submenus, change menu icons, and hide entries — "
"configured in the Menu tab. Off restores the native WordPress menu (your "
"saved layout is kept)."
msgstr ""

#: inc/class-settings-catalog.php:90
msgid "Hide admin footer"
msgstr ""

#: inc/class-settings-catalog.php:91
msgid ""
"Hide the admin footer bar — the \"Thank you for creating with WordPress\" "
"line and the version number — on every screen, for a cleaner app-like look. "
"Off restores it."
msgstr ""

#: inc/class-settings-catalog.php:96
msgid "Hide the Help button"
msgstr ""

#: inc/class-settings-catalog.php:97
msgid ""
"Hide the contextual \"Help\" tab at the top-right of admin screens, for "
"cleaner chrome. \"Screen Options\" is left in place. Off restores it."
msgstr ""

#: inc/class-settings-catalog.php:102
msgid "Users quick edit"
msgstr ""

#: inc/class-settings-catalog.php:103
msgid ""
"Edit first name, last name, email and role inline from the users list — no "
"need to open the full profile."
msgstr ""

#: inc/class-settings-catalog.php:108
msgid "Username changer"
msgstr ""

#: inc/class-settings-catalog.php:109
msgid ""
"Lets admins rename a user's login on Users → Edit (WordPress disables this "
"by default). Sensitive — invalidates the user's active sessions; they must "
"sign in again. Single-site only."
msgstr ""

#: inc/class-settings-catalog.php:114
msgid "Custom avatars"
msgstr ""

#: inc/class-settings-catalog.php:115
msgid ""
"Adds \"AdminKit Portraits (Generated)\" to Settings → Discussion → Default "
"Avatar. Pick it there to give every user a unique generated portrait."
msgstr ""

#: inc/class-settings-catalog.php:122
msgid "Bricks builder"
msgstr ""

#: inc/class-settings-catalog.php:123
msgid ""
"Restyle the Bricks builder UI with your tokens. Automatically sets Bricks → "
"Settings → Builder mode to \"Custom\"."
msgstr ""

#: inc/class-settings-catalog.php:125
msgid "Activate the Bricks theme to use this."
msgstr ""

